Senator Dino Melaye, formerly representing Kogi West in the National Assembly on the judgment of the Court of Appeal which upheld the election of Senator Smart Adeyemi of the All Progressives Congress (APC) sent a strong word to Governor Yahaya Bello of Kogi State and the beneficiary of the judgment that it is not celebration yet. The former senator admonished them that he is coming back stronger, declaring that he is not quitting yet.
Dino Melaye had maintained that the game will be different when he comes back to Kogi politics. He simply stated that he is too young to quit politics at the moment, and the judgment of the court cannot deter him. Melaye had in a tweet on his twitter handle written: #KogiWest: “I’m too young to quit. No retreat, no surrender.”